              Guide</a> </font><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Tahoma" size="2">&gt;</font><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Tahoma" size="3">
              Guide Details</font></b></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2">
              </td>
          </tr>

<tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><img border="0" src="../triangle.JPG"><font size="3" face="Tahoma" color="#004242"><b>HUNTING THE HERMIT</b></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Group / Solo:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Solo - Magician</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Mob Level:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">20</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Zone:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Karana, South</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Location:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">+2500, -6000</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Character Level:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">17 to 26</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Strategy:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">The hermit is in a house in South Karana near the south eastern edge of the zone.  The house itself is surrounded by a wall.  He spawns every 3 minutes, and drops occasional fine steel, 1-3pp, and the occasional word.
<br><br>
There are two ways to hunt him.  You can either sit inside the walls or outside.  If you sit inside the wall, you can bring him down more easily, but you run the risk of being attacked by the occasional Tesch'Mal Gnoll or Werewolf.  At these levels, solo, you will die if that happens.
<br><br>
Outside, the battle is much tougher, but you generally can see the gnoll or werewolf and get away.  Your choice.
<br><br>
Personally, I hunted inside the walls.  If you sit as close as possible to the chimney of the house, you have a better chance of avoiding the gnoll or werewolf.
<br><br>
Use either your earth or water pet.  I started with Earth at lower levels, and started using water at 20th.  The difficulty is in keeping up with the spawn rate.  It's a tough fight, so I recommend medding to full each time rather than trying to take him with less than full mana.
<br><br>
You can't get into the house.  I once saw a druid do it with treeform, but magicians just can't.  Instead, when you hear the hermit spawn, get up to the corner of the chimney where it meets the wall, and say "kill you".  This will agro the hermit on you, and he will start trying to come through the wall to you.  You may have to do this on either side of the chimney to get it to work.
<br><br>
Back up and start nuking like mad with DD.  Don't try bolt spells.  Your pet should have engaged the hermit at this point and will be in furious battle.  Nuke as hard and as fast as you can, because your pet won't last long.  Don't let the hermit get close to you because he hits in the 40's and casts druid spells.
<br><br>
At 17th, expect to use a complete bar of mana and maybe lose your pet.  As I said, don't try to keep up with the spawn before 20th.  You want to wait until 17th for this camp because you won't fizzle as much.  3 fizzles in a row can kill you.
<br><br>
At 20th, you'll use about 3 bubbles of mana and will be able to keep up with the spawn if you use a water pet.  The downside of the water pet is that you'll be more liable to being personally attacked by the hermit.  The upside is that your pet will heal on its own in time for the next spawn rather than requiring you to heal it.
<br><br>
The loot and xp is amazing, primarily due to the 3 minute spawn rate.  Once you get this spawn down, you'll rack up 1-2 bubbles an hour easily, and anywhere from 20-30pp in coin and FS weapons while doing it.  In fact, you won't want to leave to go sell :-)
<br><br>
I've heard people say that he gives good xp to 26 or so, but I left at 24th.  At 24th, my water pet could solo him.</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Author:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Eloina Pyromancer (Cazic Thule)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rating:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><b>7</b> (average of <b>12</b> votes)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left" valign="middle"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rate this spot:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left" valign="middle"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><FORM ACTION = "ratehg.asp" METHOD = post><SELECT NAME="Voting"><OPTION VALUE="0">Rate this Spot</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="1">1 - Don't even bother</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="2">2</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="3">3</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="4">4</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="5">5 - It is ok</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="6">6</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="7">7</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="8">8</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="9">9</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="10">10 - You must come here</OPTION></SELECT><INPUT TYPE = "hidden" NAME = "intHGID" VALUE = 88><INPUT TYPE = "submit" VALUE="Rate It!"></form></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan=